# Salary Calculator (Java)

A Java 17 salary calculator designed to explore clean architecture, object-oriented design, and financial modelling.

This project is built as a **core domain application**, with future plans to integrate into a Spring Boot backend.

---

## 🎯 Purpose

* Practice object-oriented design (OOP)
* Build a layered architecture
* Handle financial calculations correctly using `BigDecimal`
* Design a system that can scale into a backend service

---

## 🧱 Project Structure

```
src/main/java/
├── model/      # Domain objects (IncomeProfile, TaxBreakdown, enums)
├── service/    # Orchestration logic
├── tax/        # Tax calculation strategies
├── ui/         # CLI interface
└── SalaryCalculatorApp.java  # Main entry point
```

---

## 🧠 Architecture Overview

```
IncomeProfile (input model)
        ↓
SalaryService (orchestration)
        ↓
TaxStrategy (calculation logic)
        ↓
TaxBreakdown (output model)
```

---

## ⚙️ Tech Stack

* Java 17
* Maven
* SLF4J + Logback (logging)
* JUnit (testing)

> Spring Boot integration is planned for future backend/API development.

---

## 🚀 Getting Started

### Compile

```
mvn compile
```

### Run tests

```
mvn test
```

---

## 📌 Current Status

* [x] Project setup (Maven, structure, logging)
* [ ] IncomeProfile model
* [ ] Validation logic
* [ ] Tax strategy implementation
* [ ] CLI interface

---

## 🧠 Key Design Principles

* Immutable domain models
* Separation of concerns
* Strategy pattern for tax systems
* Single source of truth (annual salary)

---

## 🔮 Future Improvements

* Spring Boot REST API
* Config-driven tax bands
* Multiple tax jurisdictions
* Web-based UI

